Edition:
Quote: [= NZC] It is a well known fact that many of the pretended Capitalists are reduced already to all but starving point. Shiners with them are something like Angels Visits, few and far between. In fact there is little or no money in the Colony except the Company's. On you Sir the (visa : versa) success of the Colony depends.
Notes: 1843 Jan 14 The Working Men of Nelson to Captain Wakefield, NZ Company Papers 208/2 in 1958 Miller Early Victorian NZ 122

